javadoc:
Compares the function tags in two programs. 
 
 Two sets of tags are considered equal if they contain the name and comment
 attributes.

methods.name: <init>
methods.comment: Generic constructor for comparing program differences.

methods.name: compare
methods.comment:
Compares two function tag lists to determine whether the first 
  tag address is effectively less than (comes before it in memory), 
  equal to (at the same spot in memory), or greater than (comes after 
  it in memory) the second comment's address.

return.comment:
-1 if the first comes before the second in memory. 
          0 if the objects are at the same spot in memory.
          1 if the first comes after the second in memory.

methods.name: isSame
methods.comment:
Returns whether the tag lists for the given functions contain 
 the same items; order is unimportant.

return.comment: true if the tags lists contain the same elements.

methods.name: getAddressSet
methods.comment: Returns the address set that contains the address for the tags.

params.name: obj
params.comment: the object being examined by this comparator.

params.name: program
params.comment: the program the object is associated with.

return.comment: address set containing the tag location.

name: FunctionTagComparator
comment:
Compares the function tags in two programs. 
 
 Two sets of tags are considered equal if they contain the name and comment
 attributes.
